ygData.msgSnippet: Not solo, but the top of the pyramid in Cazic would be good at 35 with a good group.. Nonstop high level lizards. The entrance to lower guk live side would be
ygData.messageBody:
Not solo, but the top of the pyramid in Cazic would be good at 35 with
a good group.. Nonstop high level lizards. The entrance to lower guk
live side would be good too. Frogs on either side of the zone line would
give good exp. Even the top of Sol B by the Sol A zone would be good but
I'd hold off on Sol B until you have to go there, you'll be tired of it
soon enough.

On Thu, Feb 24/00, "Reece, Tom - 25IDL G4" <g4mntofcr@...> wrote:
> From: "Reece, Tom - 25IDL G4" <g4mntofcr@...>
>
> Was wondering if there is a good place for me to solo at 35th level? Spent
> four hours in Sol A last night in a party and killed a ton of blue goblins.
> I got maybe 3/4 bar of EXP. The camp was safe but actually pretty boring.
> I'm willing to take a risk soloing if it will help me get out of 35th. I'm
> thinking about the only place for me to solo at 35 is Rathe Mtns charming
> giants against one another. Anyone got a better suggestion. Would it just
> be better to join a group in one of the dungeons or kill ogre bouncers?
>
> Galtin of E'ci
